    "description": {
      "value": "<p>The creature can inflict a curse upon its enemies. The effects, including its save, frequency, and cure, are included in the creature&rsquo;s description. If a curse allows a saving throw, it is usually a Will save (DC = 10 + 1/2 the cursing creature&rsquo;s racial HD + that creature&rsquo;s Charisma modifier; the exact DC is given in the creature&rsquo;s descriptive text). Curses can be removed through <a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; background-image: none; background-color: initial; padding: 0px; color: #ff6400; border: none;\" draggable=\"false\" data-pack=\"pf1.spells\" data-id=\"o87h8gjxevcbztgd\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; text-decoration-line: underline;\">remove curse</span></a> and similar effects.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Format</em>: <strong>Curse Name (Su)</strong> Slam&mdash;contact; <em>save</em> Will DC 14, <em>frequency</em> 1/day, <em>effect</em> 1d4 Str drain</p>\n<p><em>Location</em>: Special Attacks and individual attacks.</p>\n<p><em>Usage:</em> Replace DC and Context notes</p>",
